      "settings": {
        "main_heading": "<h2>How is Mad Honey Made?</h2>",
        "main_content": "<p>Mad honey is made by honeybees that collect nectar primarily from certain species of rhododendron flowers, which contain <a href=\"https://medicinalmadhoney.com/pages/grayanotoxin\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Grayanotoxin\">grayanotoxins</a>. Here is how the simple nectar is converted into the world’s most distinctive and geographically limited honeys.</p>",
