            "icon_alt_text": "Icon Description",
            "icon_title": "Giant Nectar Loving Honeybees",
            "icon_description": "Apis laboriosa or as the locals call it, “The Himalayan Giant Honeybee”, is the world’s largest honey bee species that builds hives in the mountain forests. Their giant colonies store litres of honey in a single hive and guard it dearly. Gurungs use specific local plants to disorient the bees during the harvesting window. This way, harvesters save themselves from the attack of the bees.",
